Aujeszky's disease [pseudorabies], France
-----------------------------------------
Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Started: 28 Sep 2021
Confirmed: 29 Sep 2021
Reported: 7 Oct 2021
Reason for notification: Recurrence
Last occurrence: 14 Apr 2021
Causal agent: Aujeszky's disease virus
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak location 1: Segonzac, Brive-la-Gaillarde, Correze, Nouvelle-Aquitaine
Started: 28 Sep 2021
Epidemiological unit: farm
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered or killed for commercial use / Vaccinated
Wild boar (_Sus scrofa_): Suidae-Artiodactyla / 70 / 1 / 0 / - / - / 0
Affected population: identification of contamination with Aujeszky's disease virus in a farm of wild boar intended for release into the wild for hunting (one positive animal out of 15 sampled). No clinical signs.

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive, contact with wild species
Epidemiological comments: epidemiological investigation in progress; a contact with wildlife fellows is likely.

Control measures
Control measures applied in domestic: movement control inside the country; surveillance within containment and or the protection zone; traceability; zoning; disinfection
Control measures to be applied in domestic: stamping out; slaughter

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Anses -- Laboratoire de Ploufragan-Plouzan√©-Niort -- site de Ploufragan (national laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Wild boar / Enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) / 29 Sep 2021 / Positive

